version_description: This version of the song elaborates on some of the parts that aren't included in the easier versions. It is a more complex, but more whole representation of the song. Intermediate- includes barres, but they are easy. Parts of this version like the strumming pattern, and the rap are hard to grasp without playing along to the song alot. Memorize the chords first, then play along to the song on youtube.

I tried to learn this song by ear and I think this song has a lot of chord changes. It might be weird if people see this tab for the first time because of all the chords. I think a lot of people get disctracted by the pinao riff when they try to play along for the first time. The intro switching from Am to G shows that this song isn't monotone at all.
More accurate timing and chord voicing.
The chorus of the version that's there is inaccurate. It gives a completely wrong tone. Also, the bridge part 2 (or whatever it's called...) is almost right but not entirely accurate.
